        "label": "What's Going On With the Leafs",
        "body": "The Leafs' desert swing turned into a masterclass in late-season dominance, shaking off the ghosts of that Vegas slip with back-to-back shutdowns that silenced doubters. <strong>Anthony Stolarz stonewalled Calgary 3-1 Tuesday night</strong>, his 35 saves in the Apr 15 rout capping a 2-1 grinder over Edmonton the night before &mdash; a timely reminder that this 54-16-11 juggernaut, perched atop the Central with 78 points and 35 games clear of the pack, isn't fading into the playoff seed 15 shadows just yet. Nylander's been the quiet engine, his 29 goals and 48 assists fueling the fire amid whispers of Tavares carrying the load with 71 points, while the blue line &mdash; battered by injuries &mdash; held firm without a single defensive lapse. That L6 streak? Ancient history now. The real test looms <strong>Friday in Seattle against the Kraken</strong>, where a third straight win could lock in home ice and ignite the Cup talk Toronto craves. This machine rolls on.",
        "updated": "Updated April 15, 2026"
      },
