    "jays": {
      "full_name": "Toronto Blue Jays",
      "league": "MLB",
      "record": "7-9",
      "detail": "4th in AL East",
      "live_strip": null,
      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Jays",
        "body": "In the dim dawn of another AL East scrap, the Blue Jays clawed back from the brink Monday night, erupting for <strong>a 9-7 thriller over the Brewers</strong> that snapped a two-game skid to the Twins and nudged their record to 7-9, fourth place, 3 games back. Vlad Guerrero Jr. owned the night&mdash;53 at-bats, 17 hits, a homer, six runs driven in&mdash;his bat a sledgehammer amid the chaos of a sloppy series where Milwaukee's young gun Jacob Misiorowski couldn't contain the fire. It's the first win in four tries against the Brewers this young season, a gasp of oxygen for a squad that's flickered more than flamed, with Darin Varsho, the Wisconsin kid, stroking key hits in the upset. No major injuries biting yet, but the trade whispers from last week linger like bad hops. Tonight's rubber game at Milwaukee&mdash;6:40 ET&mdash;looms as the tell: <strong>can they steal the series from a Brew Crew on its own five-game skid, or does Misiorowski remind them why the East chews up pretenders?</strong> This road test matters; it's the pivot before the Angels beckon.",
        "updated": "Updated April 15, 2026"
      },
