    "raptors": {
      "full_name": "Toronto Raptors",
      "league": "NBA",
      "record": "46-36",
      "detail": "3rd in Atlantic Division",
      "live_strip": null,
      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Raptors",
        "body": "The Raptors clawed their way back from the brink, refusing to let another season slip into the abyss of mediocrity. <strong>Scottie Barnes erupted for 32 points and 12 rebounds in Tuesday's gritty 112-105 win over the Knicks</strong>, snapping a mini-slump and vaulting Toronto to 46-36, good for third in the Atlantic and the no. 5 playoff seed with a one-game win streak. It's the kind of night that silences the doubters &mdash; Barnes, the 24-year-old cornerstone, has been a force since returning from that nagging ankle tweak, averaging 28 over his last three while Immanuel Quickley dishes dimes like it's 2019 all over again. No major injuries derailing this run; the bench finally showed spine after months of head-scratching trades that left Masai Ujiri's vision under the microscope. Five games back of the Atlantic lead? Sure, but in a conference this muddled, momentum is oxygen. The ghosts of 2019 playoffs still whisper promise. <strong>Watch tonight's play-in showdown against the Hawks</strong> &mdash; win, and it's a home first-round date; lose, and the summer starts early. This group's got unfinished business.",
        "updated": "Updated April 15, 2026"
      },
