      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Commanders",
        "body": "The Commanders' season-long slog through the NFC East meat grinder finally coughed up a parting gift &mdash; a gritty road win that felt more like defiance than destiny. <strong>Washington's 24-17 gut-punch over the Eagles on Jan. 4</strong> snapped a two-game skid, with the defense stuffing Jalen Hurts on fourth-and-short late, preserving a victory that rang hollow amid the ruins of a 5-12 finish. Sitting third in the division, nine games back, on a one-game win streak &mdash; it's the definition of too little, too late for a squad that teased playoffs before crumbling. Jayden Daniels dazzled in flashes, his arm whipping 320 yards and two scores against Philly, but the rookie QB's turnovers doomed earlier collapses; now, whispers of a sophomore slump linger as he eyes the draft. Terry McLaurin? Silent assassin with six grabs for 92 yards last time out, carrying the load while injuries sidelined the line. Offseason looms large &mdash; free agency opens next week, and with the top pick a pipe dream at No. 14 seed, GM Adam Peters hunts edge rushers. <strong>Watch the mock drafts: LSU corner Mansoor Delane could lock down the secondary if they trade up.</strong> This rebuild's got teeth &mdash; or it better.",
